data.name: buttonResetAPIKey.ToolTip
data.value: Reset the API key to clear the current key and allow you to enter a new one.

data.name: buttonUpdateAPIKey.ToolTip
data.value: Save the API key in API key field. If you change the API key, you need to click this button to save it.

data.name: buttonShowHide.ToolTip
data.value: Show the API key in the API key field. Click again to hide it.

data.name: labelAPIKeyWarning.Text
data.value: Warning: For your security, do not share your Google Gemini™ API key with anyone else.

data.name: textBoxAPIKey.ToolTip
data.value: Set your API key here to use the AI music generation feature. You can get your API key from https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey.

data.name: btn_test_system_speaker.ToolTip
data.value: This button plays a short tune through the system speaker to test the system speaker on your computer.

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message.Text
data.value: If you do not hear any sound, you can use the "Use sound device to create beep" feature.

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message_2.Text
data.value: Testing the system speaker is not available on computers that do not have a system speaker output, or on computers with a non-standard system speaker output.

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message_3.Text
data.value: On compact computers and computers of unknown type, you may not hear any sound or may cause instability or undesirable behavior when the system speaker is tested because the main speakers may be connected to the system speaker output instead of the actual system speaker.

data.name: checkBox_enable_create_beep_from_soundcard.Text
data.value: Use sound device to create beep

data.name: checkBox_enable_create_beep_from_soundcard.ToolTip
data.value: Use sound device instead of system speaker to create beep

data.name: group_beep_creation_from_sound_card_settings.Text
data.value: Beep Creation from Sound Device Settings

data.name: label_create_beep_from_soundcard_automatically_activated_message_1.Text
data.value: The "Use sound device to create beep" feature is permanently enabled because the system speaker output is not detected, or the system speaker output is non-standard.

data.name: label_create_beep_from_soundcard_automatically_activated_message_2.Text
data.value: The "Use sound device to create beep" feature is automatically enabled because the computer is a compact computer or its type is unknown.

data.name: button_show_reason.Text
data.value: Show the reason for this situation

data.name: checkBox_use_midi_input.ToolTip
data.value: Use MIDI input device to send notes to the NeoBleeper. If you have a MIDI keyboard, you can use it to play notes on the NeoBleeper.

data.name: refresh_midi_input_button.ToolTip
data.value: Refresh the list of MIDI input devices

data.name: comboBox_midi_input_devices.ToolTip
data.value: Select the MIDI input device you want to use. If you have multiple devices, select the one you want to use for input.

data.name: checkBox_use_midi_output.ToolTip
data.value: Use MIDI output device to play notes. This will allow you to use external MIDI devices or software synthesizers.

data.name: comboBox_midi_output_instrument.ToolTip
data.value: Select the instrument to be used for MIDI output The instrument will be used for all MIDI output.

data.name: comboBox_midi_output_channel.ToolTip
data.value: Select MIDI channel for output. If you are not sure, leave it as is.

data.name: refresh_midi_output_button.ToolTip
data.value: Refresh the list of MIDI output devices

data.name: comboBox_midi_output_devices.ToolTip
data.value: Select the MIDI output device to use for sending notes. If you have a MIDI device connected, it should appear here.

data.name: trackBar_motor_octave.ToolTip
data.value: Set the octave for the motor. The motor will run at a speed corresponding to the selected octave. 0 = lowest speed, 5 = highest speed.

data.name: radioButtonBuzzer.ToolTip
data.value: Buzzer is a device that can produce sound by vibrating a diaphragm or a piezoelectric element. It is often used in alarms, timers, and other devices that require sound output.

data.name: radioButtonMotor.ToolTip
data.value: Motor is used to create tones by changing the speed of the motor.

data.name: checkBox_use_microcontroller.Text
data.value: Use Motor-speed mod or buzzer (via Arduino, Raspberry Pi or ESP32)

data.name: checkBox_use_microcontroller.ToolTip
data.value: Use microcontroller to use with motor or buzzer. If you use motor, you can control speed of it with motor speed mod slider.
